39:15.364 --> 39:17.567
They would listen to MP3s, listen to a lot of sermons.

39:17.587 --> 39:21.954
And video came along, and now the video is the pixels and all that captured us with video.

39:22.895 --> 39:27.122
And there's good that can be done through watching video, through listening.

39:27.234 --> 39:35.964
I would encourage you to devote, you call it this, diversify the portfolio of how you receive God's word into your heart.

39:36.885 --> 39:40.349
If you're not a reader, I would say, work on that, you know, add reading.

39:40.389 --> 39:47.977
And if you're not doing any kind of audio, I'd say think about how the Holy Spirit may have some blessing for you in hearing with faith.

39:48.578 --> 39:49.119
Great question.

39:50.901 --> 39:52.082
Great question, thank you.

39:52.194 --> 39:56.399
One of my favorite chapters in your book is actually about memorizing scripture.

39:56.419 --> 40:01.344
And so I would love for you to just talk about memorizing scripture and how that like benefits us and that's helpful for us.

40:01.745 --> 40:02.045
Thanks.

40:02.065 --> 40:02.706
Thank you so much.

40:03.026 --> 40:14.379
I mean, the, uh, in the book and still believe this fully, uh, I really made memorizing scripture to overlap with the idea of meditation.

40:15.019 --> 40:20.946
So that middle of like reading Bible, meditating on God's word and then prayer.

40:21.026 --> 40:22.028
coming out of meditation.

40:22.628 --> 40:24.872
I really put memorizing here in meditation.

40:24.952 --> 40:33.345
And the power of memorization, of memorizing scripture, is not simply that you have it stored away for the future.

40:33.445 --> 40:37.331
I know sometimes we talk that way and it's like, if you don't memorize it now, you're not gonna have it.

40:37.772 --> 40:38.953
12 years from now, you need it.

40:39.755 --> 40:45.564
And just to be honest with you, I'm not really motivated by, well, someday maybe I might need it.

40:46.645 --> 40:49.810
I got too many demands today.

40:50.466 --> 40:53.049
to give a bunch of time to someday maybes.

40:54.430 --> 41:03.941
I'm mainly am interested in, I wanna know Jesus today, I wanna delight in him today, I wanna feed my soul today, I wanna feast like I say at 55 today.

41:04.301 --> 41:10.608
So if scripture memory can serve meditation today, I'm seeking delight in Jesus today.

41:11.108 --> 41:20.018
I came across a verse that was so good, I didn't only meditate on it with it written in front of me, I was like, I should just memorize this.

41:20.450 --> 41:22.513
then I can just chew on this all day.

41:22.593 --> 41:29.201
So I would encourage you, let your memorization be inspired by some really sweet text.

41:29.742 --> 41:35.129
You come across in your devotional readings like, man, the Lord met me in half a verse.

41:36.110 --> 41:46.604
And I could memorize that half verse in 15 seconds and rehearse it throughout the day and keep enjoying Jesus in that little God-inspired, memorized statement from scripture.

41:47.205 --> 41:47.986
And so I would say,

41:48.194 --> 41:51.799
use memorization as a way to feed meditation.

41:52.720 --> 41:57.907
And also, I mean, in campus ministry, sometimes it is a wonderful thing when you memorize scripture together.

41:58.908 --> 42:03.534
So when you can do it as a community, hey, we're working on this together, we're enjoying this together, memorize it.

42:03.594 --> 42:07.199
And I would say as you memorize scripture, don't just check the box, like I got it done.

42:07.759 --> 42:10.983
Like I can say it wrote.

42:12.586 --> 42:13.206
That's not the point.

42:13.667 --> 42:16.050
The point is now you got something to enjoy.

42:16.642 --> 42:22.451
And most of us, we tend to forget scripture memory precision over time.

42:23.333 --> 42:25.016
And sometimes they're like, oh no, this is a problem.

42:25.737 --> 42:26.258
Such a problem.

42:26.278 --> 42:30.204
Like I memorized Romans eight and now I don't know it precisely.

42:30.224 --> 42:32.147
And it's like, oh no, what a loss.

42:32.187 --> 42:32.908
I wasted time.

42:32.928 --> 42:34.130
And I was like, no, no, no.

42:34.611 --> 42:38.377
That's an opportunity that you don't know it perfectly still.

42:38.477 --> 42:39.058
Hey, that's great.

42:39.419 --> 42:41.362
Now you can go back to it and join it some more.

42:41.474 --> 42:43.837
Work on it some more, sharpen it up, feed your heart.

42:44.298 --> 42:48.924
So if scripture is memorized and you forget it, that is not a loss.

42:49.465 --> 42:51.007
That's actually an opportunity to do some more.

42:51.327 --> 43:02.162
But I would want to emphasize, how can you enjoy the living God and Jesus Christ right now in lingering over scripture long enough that it gets put to memory?

43:03.234 --> 43:03.875
That's so good.

43:03.915 --> 43:07.218
I'm so glad you said that because I remember reading that chapter for the first time.

43:07.298 --> 43:15.365
And so much of like, when we talk about memorizing scriptures, like, oh, this is for later, but you actually like flip it of like, it actually could benefit me right now.

43:15.506 --> 43:20.510
Like there is like a benefit and it's helpful to just meditate on it right now as I'm memorizing.

43:20.530 --> 43:21.571
So I love that.

43:22.372 --> 43:27.757
One question that came in is how do you re-remember your time in the word throughout the day intentionally?

43:28.758 --> 43:30.720
Great question.

43:30.740 --> 43:32.882
The first thing I would say is,

43:33.442 --> 43:35.985
If there's that space, that bridge.

43:36.806 --> 43:38.748
Sorry, I'm laughing because I got a funny question.

43:39.208 --> 43:40.349
Okay, all right, let's do the funny question.

43:41.351 --> 43:58.009
That bridge between Bible reading and prayer, if I linger there, if I spend some time there, what I'm seeking to do, I'm seeking to drive that moment into my psyche, into my consciousness, make that be my perspective on the day.

43:58.029 --> 44:02.994
Something I say more about is I threw out that number 10 minutes

44:03.490 --> 44:06.334
that if you read the Bible 10 minutes a day, you'll read it in a year.

44:07.316 --> 44:17.131
So here's one way you could approach this is during that 10 minutes of reading, now you get down with the reading, it's like, huh, what struck me from that reading?

44:17.752 --> 44:19.134
And was there like a particular verse?

44:19.554 --> 44:20.676
It could have been half a verse?

44:21.557 --> 44:22.839
It could be a word.

44:22.900 --> 44:30.812
The word, it's not simply a word, but the word represents a concept in which God is communing with you.

44:30.832 --> 44:32.434
He's speaking to you that day.

44:32.770 --> 44:33.991
you were struck by something.

44:34.332 --> 44:36.514
And I would say, so what if you get the 10 minutes of reading?

44:36.894 --> 44:38.596
Now what if you take, I'll throw out another number.

44:39.517 --> 44:40.518
What if you double that time?

44:40.698 --> 44:48.827
I'm gonna take 10 minutes and I'm gonna linger over that thing that struck me, the thing that stood out in my reading.

44:49.548 --> 44:50.949
I might even journal some thought.

44:50.970 --> 44:52.211
This could be a place for journaling.

44:52.872 --> 44:54.213
This could be a place for memorization.

44:55.034 --> 45:02.642
So one way to take it with you is, if it's short, just memorize it right there versus throughout the day.

45:02.722 --> 45:07.026
My generation, we still use paper, or at least I do, right?

45:07.106 --> 45:09.128
I brought my notes here on paper.

45:09.148 --> 45:10.610
I read a paper Bible in the morning.

45:10.630 --> 45:12.232
One thing about paper, it just slows you down.

45:12.852 --> 45:17.036
A screen tends to make you read a little bit faster on a screen.

45:17.076 --> 45:18.157
Scientists have studied this.

45:18.738 --> 45:23.503
When you read papers, you get these precious milliseconds that it slows you down.

45:23.963 --> 45:25.044
You might think a little more.

45:25.064 --> 45:25.965
It might go into the heart.

45:26.766 --> 45:28.588
And sometimes I'll jot a note.

45:28.608 --> 45:30.770
I have a little notebook I keep with me.

45:30.946 --> 45:32.628
I'll jot a note on paper.

45:33.088 --> 45:40.336
If I have written it down, or if I've prayed it, this is where you can write out prayers.

45:41.216 --> 45:41.777
It's a beautiful thing.

45:41.837 --> 45:45.201
Pick something from your reading that really struck you, write it out.

45:46.041 --> 45:51.988
And then when you do pray, pray about the way in which God was speaking to you through His words.

45:52.028 --> 45:57.133
I mean, if you're reading for 10 minutes, you're not gonna pray over everything you read in those 10 minutes.

45:57.753 --> 45:58.354
You may pick

45:59.906 --> 46:02.169
a light bulb or two that went off.

46:03.512 --> 46:11.564
And as you move through thinking on that and then praying on it, hopefully you're putting it deeper into your soul, at least for that day.

46:11.584 --> 46:22.020
And you may, you're gonna forget probably in a week, like three days later, a week later, hey, what was your sweet thought about God last Monday morning?

46:22.040 --> 46:27.228
It's like, I don't know, but I still believe it fed me last Monday.

46:27.248 --> 46:28.690
I got through the day.

46:28.770 --> 46:33.275
And I think if you spent long enough feeding on it, you're probably going to remember it later that afternoon.

46:35.417 --> 46:35.737
All right, fun.

46:35.757 --> 46:36.678
You get the funny question?

46:36.738 --> 46:39.061
Yeah, we don't have time for that.

46:39.081 --> 46:42.164
It's just from down here.

46:42.264 --> 46:43.225
Yeah, you know who you are.

46:43.245 --> 46:46.929
OK, I'm just going to read this off for you.

46:47.389 --> 46:47.449
OK.

46:47.469 --> 46:50.272
When reading scriptures, some chapters can be super hard to understand.

46:50.312 --> 46:52.514
Should I immediately look to commentary?

46:52.595 --> 46:53.816
Or do I go back to it again?

46:53.856 --> 46:56.018
Oh, that's a great question.

46:56.610 --> 46:58.974
This is, this is both.

46:59.935 --> 47:08.809
I know initially it's a frustration, but let me tell you somebody who's been reading the Bible now since, because they convinced me in college.

47:08.869 --> 47:17.122
Like I set in groups like this and we talked about reading the Bible and so 25 years ago, I learned to just make the simple habit, simple habit.

47:17.943 --> 47:20.687
And it is amazing how it compounds over time.

47:21.228 --> 47:25.074
And so while it may be a frustration in your twenties,

47:25.442 --> 47:30.227
you're going to be so thankful in your 40s and your 50s that you didn't just get it all the first time.

47:31.028 --> 47:36.073
So you really should have some modest expectations for Bible reading.

47:36.093 --> 47:39.957
When I say, you know, you're reading 10 minutes or whatever it is, there is no pretense.

47:40.338 --> 47:46.604
You're going to understand or understand well everything, but especially when you get deep into the prophets.

47:46.644 --> 47:48.726
Like I've been reading Isaiah this month.

47:49.007 --> 47:52.370
I got on the docket for next month Ezekiel.

47:52.546 --> 47:54.008
Like this is some hard stuff.

47:54.028 --> 47:56.431
This is one reason to get multiple places in the Bible.

47:56.992 --> 47:58.073
So I'm also reading in a gospel.

47:58.213 --> 48:00.696
And usually the gospel is pretty immediate.

48:01.898 --> 48:03.740
Or the book of Psalms is often more immediate.

48:03.760 --> 48:06.664
So starting with a Psalm or with the gospel can help.

48:07.044 --> 48:09.928
And then, hey, you're making your way through the Old Testament text.

48:09.948 --> 48:12.331
And sometimes something pops from the Old Testament.

48:12.411 --> 48:13.372
It is clear as day.

48:13.412 --> 48:14.333
It is amazing.

48:14.614 --> 48:15.455
You linger over it.

48:15.775 --> 48:18.899
And often you're building up a reservoir.

48:19.119 --> 48:21.202
You're learning to read the Bible for a lifetime.

48:21.570 --> 48:29.260
And I would say, when you can do some study, when something rises to the level, your triage is different as you age.

48:29.701 --> 48:40.696
If you're reading the Bible through for the first time in your 20s, just to say, there's gonna be a lot of stuff that's difficult, that's foreign, that doesn't immediately fit for you.

48:41.176 --> 48:44.080
And so you gotta decide what you're gonna study.

48:45.522 --> 48:49.467
You won't have enough time to look up every question you could ask.

48:49.968 --> 48:51.570
If you're curious and you're astute,

48:51.778 --> 48:54.020
you can ask way more questions than you can answer.

48:54.921 --> 49:01.828
But as you keep reading, day after day, year after year, pieces come together, pieces come together.

49:01.848 --> 49:03.770
Not in such a way you ever are mastered by this book.

49:04.010 --> 49:05.852
You are seeking to be mastered by it.

49:06.512 --> 49:14.079
And so by putting yourself in and under the Bible's authority day after day, the Holy Spirit, He's gonna find some ways to feed you.

49:14.099 --> 49:20.946
There's some simple things here, simple for children, simple for teens and 20s and 30s and 45 year olds like me.

49:21.122 --> 49:24.507
And some other things that take scholars that they work on in their 60s and 70s.

49:26.569 --> 49:31.796
The Bible is like an ocean that a child can wait into and elephant can drown in.

49:33.158 --> 49:35.301
And so have that perspective in mind.

49:35.381 --> 49:37.644
And as you come to a question like, I want to look that up.

49:37.764 --> 49:38.445
I've got time.

49:39.026 --> 49:40.048
I've got margin this morning.

49:40.088 --> 49:40.989
I'd like to look it up.

49:41.750 --> 49:43.552
There's some excellent study Bibles out there.

49:43.572 --> 49:45.074
The ESV study Bible is very good.

49:45.094 --> 49:46.216
There's other study Bibles.

49:46.576 --> 49:50.802
A study Bible can get you quickly to a meaning without flipping through a lot.

49:51.394 --> 49:53.156
Also, there's commentaries out there.

49:53.196 --> 49:55.037
There's amazing resources online.

49:55.618 --> 50:00.903
I would recommend desiringgod.org as one place where you can look up questions.

50:01.684 --> 50:15.537
And you learn to pray for the Holy Spirit's guidance that he would give you wisdom and triaging among the many things that you could ask questions about and learn to know which one is for today.

50:17.079 --> 50:20.562
One of my favorite phrases is in coming to the Bible.

50:20.770 --> 50:24.214
This is from Exodus chapter 15.

50:24.234 --> 50:26.176
I think it's from Exodus chapter 16.

50:27.438 --> 50:30.601
And the manna is given to the children of Israel in the wilderness.

50:31.182 --> 50:34.926
And the instructions are, every day, gather a day's portion.

50:36.388 --> 50:37.329
Don't get a week's portion.

50:37.769 --> 50:39.411
You don't go out and try to gather enough for a month.

50:39.791 --> 50:40.572
It's not going to keep.

50:40.793 --> 50:42.014
It doesn't mean for you to do it.

50:42.935 --> 50:45.618
And right now as college students, there could be this sense of like,

50:45.858 --> 50:47.260
I need to gather enough for a lifetime.

50:47.280 --> 50:49.484
I gotta go, I gotta forge my theology.

50:49.504 --> 50:51.567
I gotta find out what I believe about every issue.

50:51.627 --> 50:54.913
And I would just say, gather a day's portion.

50:55.994 --> 50:57.477
What's gonna feed you today?

50:57.497 --> 51:03.567
And as you feed on the living God day after day, he's gonna answer all sorts of questions.

51:04.348 --> 51:06.111
And it's gonna be good to still have some questions.

51:06.191 --> 51:13.202
If this book is really from God, you're not gonna read in your 20s and understand all of it, or close to all of it, but it's a lifelong journey.

51:13.890 --> 51:14.431
That's good.

51:14.451 --> 51:14.871
That's awesome.

51:14.891 --> 51:16.314
It's a really helpful perspective.

51:17.155 --> 51:19.839
What do you do when you don't understand something in the Bible?

51:19.859 --> 51:23.044
I mean, triage it like that.

51:23.204 --> 51:33.900
So here at age 45, having been a seminary, I'm a pastor, I preach, part of my job is studying the Bible and writing articles and editing articles.

51:34.460 --> 51:37.745
And so I've had the opportunity over the years to look into some of these questions and study them.

51:38.747 --> 51:43.634
But daily, I come across, I could formulate more questions daily

51:44.066 --> 51:48.711
from 10 minutes of Bible reading, then I have time to answer.

51:49.732 --> 51:51.193
And so I've learned that triaging.

51:52.534 --> 52:07.169
One of my favorite things for finding answers myself without going for help from a commentator or a study Bible is seeing where that concept appears elsewhere in scripture.

52:07.449 --> 52:12.594
And sometimes some Bibles will have this thing down the middle called cross references.

52:12.738 --> 52:18.804
You get these little tiny numbers, and as you read through, it'll refer to other verses.

52:19.885 --> 52:23.808
This is a way of letting scripture interpret scripture.

52:24.649 --> 52:29.514
Instead of just running off to have some commentator give you the answer, you can say, huh.

52:30.114 --> 52:34.819
So where else have I read about this concept, or does it come up anywhere else?

52:35.439 --> 52:38.622
And if you're a first time Bible reader, you may know very little.

52:38.662 --> 52:42.706
You can't, I don't know if this is in Genesis and Exodus or not.

52:43.106 --> 52:47.333
But as you grow over the years, you may realize, oh, okay.

52:47.353 --> 52:50.538
So this passage, there's a little study I did recently.

52:50.578 --> 52:54.685
I came across the word refresh in the book of Philemon.

52:55.706 --> 52:57.689
Paul says, refresh my soul.

52:57.749 --> 53:00.834
That's the language he gives to Philemon.

53:00.874 --> 53:04.200
He wants him to free his slave Onissimus, who's become a Christian.

53:04.560 --> 53:06.183
So his soul would be refreshed.

53:06.203 --> 53:10.610
So Paul's soul would be refreshed if Onissimus frees his life.

53:11.426 --> 53:15.330
You know, amazing thing in the first century, totally culturally surprising in the first century.

53:16.091 --> 53:19.214
And so I, what is this language of refresh comments?

53:19.254 --> 53:20.855
I looked it up in several different places.

53:20.955 --> 53:25.620
I don't remember, maybe they're eight or 10 times New Testament where you use that similar kind of language.

53:26.561 --> 53:28.943
It was remarkable how relational it was.

53:29.864 --> 53:34.629
That the refreshing of souls, it didn't have like a wilderness context.

53:35.249 --> 53:38.092
It usually had a very relational context.

53:38.132 --> 53:40.114
Like I met a person

53:40.802 --> 53:45.307
that I love from far away and we spent time together and our souls were refreshed.

53:46.348 --> 53:50.213
It's like how fellowship, how community, how gatherings like this are means of God's grace.

53:50.914 --> 53:54.398
And so I didn't run to a commentator to try to figure out the answer.

53:54.938 --> 54:02.527
I wanted some other scripture text and it is amazing how the biblical authors speak with a unified voice.

54:03.628 --> 54:07.373
You will find differences between like, okay, that's Paul and that's John.

54:07.453 --> 54:08.594
Like John and Paul,

54:08.802 --> 54:09.723
They're different.

54:09.743 --> 54:11.364
Like John kind of talks in circles.

54:11.425 --> 54:12.906
And some of us are like, that's beautiful.

54:13.006 --> 54:13.426
I love that.

54:13.446 --> 54:14.067
It's really helpful.

54:14.628 --> 54:16.489
And Paul's like, he's always in a straight line.

54:16.890 --> 54:17.530
Really logical.

54:17.891 --> 54:18.691
Here's the reason for it.

54:18.932 --> 54:19.933
Here's the implication for it.

54:19.953 --> 54:21.314
And other people are like, I really like Paul.

54:22.435 --> 54:25.518
And God means for us to be blessed and benefit by both of them.

54:26.018 --> 54:30.863
But then at the end of the day, their concepts come together in this amazing unified whole.

54:30.923 --> 54:38.130
And you will find this from Moses to David and Solomon and to the prophets and to the gospels.

54:38.210 --> 54:46.680
and the epistles, that they're these unifying themes throughout the Bible, that it is this library, even though 66 books, all these different authors.

54:46.941 --> 54:57.814
The library is telling one whole story, and those pieces come together in a beautiful way, and so you can explore those themes, not only in that author, but the other biblical authors.

54:58.595 --> 54:59.156
That's awesome.

55:00.017 --> 55:03.281
How do you fight through seasons where it feels like reading your Bible is a chore?

55:05.123 --> 55:07.346
Good question.

55:09.474 --> 55:11.857
I would say a couple of different things I can say.

55:13.239 --> 55:24.174
One is it is worth continuing to expose yourself to the place where the grace is coming and it's going to come.

55:25.256 --> 55:38.834
So if you were to say, what do I do when I'm not thirsty?

55:39.266 --> 55:47.720
I would not tell you to turn away from the waterfall and dig into the ground and try to like put the dirt in your mouth.

55:49.903 --> 55:52.007
You still need to orient toward the waterfall.

55:52.067 --> 55:54.511
That's where the life-giving water is going to be.

55:55.292 --> 56:00.340
Your thirst needs to adjust to the objective truth of the water.

56:00.881 --> 56:02.945
And that happens to all of us, okay?

56:03.225 --> 56:03.926
We're sinners.

56:04.106 --> 56:04.748
We're finite.

56:05.469 --> 56:06.290
We're sinners.

56:06.882 --> 56:16.652
When we don't have a taste for God's word, if we don't want him, if we can't even like, thought of enjoying him or delighting in him is so foreign.

56:17.412 --> 56:19.655
Maybe the best I can do is that I want to want.

56:20.576 --> 56:23.919
But ultimately, that's not a problem with God's word.

56:24.740 --> 56:26.421
That's a problem with me.

56:26.702 --> 56:28.123
It's a problem with my sinful heart.

56:28.584 --> 56:29.204
And that's okay.

56:29.244 --> 56:30.165
Be honest about that.

56:30.205 --> 56:32.267
If your heart's there, you'd be honest about it.

56:32.287 --> 56:33.248
That's not a big surprise.

56:33.268 --> 56:34.129
We're all like that.

56:34.169 --> 56:35.090
We all have that.

56:35.682 --> 56:43.370
But don't pretend that the problems with the Bible and that my desires are the fixed, objective, unchangeable thing.

56:43.930 --> 56:44.351
No, no, no.

56:45.072 --> 56:49.436
This is the fixed, objective, unchangeable thing.

56:49.997 --> 56:52.659
And I need to have my heart adjusted.

56:52.679 --> 56:53.600
So I wanna pray for that.

56:54.101 --> 57:03.090
This is why fellowship is so beautiful that you're not just on your own, to be around other Christians, to have contagious love for Jesus spoken about, to have somebody put a word in this ear,

57:03.490 --> 57:08.495
Sometimes people desire so low, it's like, I don't, I can't go through the energy of reading this book.

57:08.896 --> 57:16.244
And that's a beautiful place where somebody can put a word in your ear that would feed your soul and help shape your desire.

57:17.045 --> 57:28.457
And another thing I would say, I wish somebody would have told me this in my 20s, that you can teach your heart over time what to focus on.

57:29.017 --> 57:33.362
As you get older, as you get older, you can learn, not everybody does.

57:34.594 --> 57:37.900
Modern life doesn't teach people to do this.

57:37.940 --> 57:39.323
This is very counter-cultural.

57:40.465 --> 57:51.565
You can learn how to manage your heart a little bit and manage with quotes because John Owen, a great Puritan, talked about managing.

57:52.386 --> 57:58.738
And as you spend day after day, week after week, year after year, beginning with Bible,

57:59.682 --> 58:10.853
Moving to meditation, one thing you learn about as you seek to meditate, to linger, to set your mind and heart on the things of God and His Word, you learn about your heart.

58:12.054 --> 58:18.060
You learn about the kinds of things to focus it on, the kinds of attributes of God, the parts of the story, the beauties of Jesus.

58:18.921 --> 58:22.605
You can learn how to take riches from this library.

58:22.625 --> 58:26.048
This is not a simple, flat little book.

58:26.068 --> 58:27.730
This is a rich library.

58:27.874 --> 58:31.779
and there are amazing resources to help all sorts of hearts.

58:32.920 --> 58:34.942
And that's one thing that we learned to do over the years.

58:35.042 --> 58:40.309
Now, there's no pretense that if this is your first time reading the Bible through that you're a master at that.

58:40.349 --> 58:48.979
I'm not a master at that at age 45, but I would tell you that after a few years and after a few decades, you learned to kind of turn this thing.

58:50.220 --> 58:52.163
You learned to say, heart?

58:53.704 --> 58:55.026
Why are you acting like that?

58:56.898 --> 59:00.944
Trusting God, hoping God is how the Psalmist talked.

59:01.845 --> 59:02.767
Are you downcast?

59:02.867 --> 59:03.608
Trusting God.

59:04.689 --> 59:06.652
Let no pretense that he goes away magically.

59:07.594 --> 59:11.139
But there's some ways you can learn where to set your heart, where to focus.

59:11.900 --> 59:24.338
And I really think that over time, as you're formed and shaped in your faith, by this book, by the Holy Spirit, that sort of experience often becomes less frequent.

59:25.218 --> 59:27.200
And take heart.

59:27.320 --> 59:31.845
If that's an experience you feel like, oh, I'm so up and down right now, you know, that's true.

59:31.925 --> 59:32.605
Be honest about it.

59:33.586 --> 59:36.809
And that doesn't mean it's going to be that way the rest of your life.

59:38.071 --> 59:42.755
Like as you are spending time with the living God in this book, he's shaping your soul.

59:43.676 --> 59:44.937
Change is really possible.

59:45.158 --> 59:50.583
You are going to be a different person in 10 years and the battle will not be the same.

59:50.863 --> 59:52.165
It'll be less frequent.

59:52.185 --> 59:53.586
That doesn't mean we're any less desperate.

59:54.082 --> 59:56.906
At the end of the day, it's the Holy Spirit and we are desperate.

59:57.688 --> 01:00:01.113
And he means for us to grow in him and he shapes us along the way.

01:00:02.094 --> 01:00:02.455
Awesome.

01:00:02.735 --> 01:00:03.036
Great.

01:00:03.176 --> 01:00:03.436
Okay.

