I know guys, there's so many good questions.

01:00:07.583 --> 01:00:16.176
It says, I often find myself treating God like he is a vending machine and like I'm throwing pennies into the pool instead of talking with someone who actually loves me.

01:00:16.737 --> 01:00:18.840
What specific truth would you give this person?

01:00:21.604 --> 01:00:22.706
That sounds of

01:00:23.362 --> 01:00:29.949
Whatever your question is, if it's that one or another one, this is amazing thing about what to bring to God's word.

01:00:31.671 --> 01:00:43.424
I would say, like I encourage you guys tonight, to come with the angle of approach of enjoyment, to say, as you're opening the Bible, to say, Father in Heaven, I want to enjoy you this morning.

01:00:43.504 --> 01:00:45.206
Would you show me yourself in your glory?

01:00:46.086 --> 01:00:48.389
I want to see what's delightful in Jesus.

01:00:48.749 --> 01:00:49.811
I want to recognize that.

01:00:49.851 --> 01:00:53.074
Would you bring my heart into shape with what you are worth?

01:00:53.890 --> 01:00:57.956
God's okay with us bringing a perspective to His Word.

01:00:58.897 --> 01:01:07.210
And if your perspective is, I'm struggling with your goodness, I'm struggling to see your love, to see you as compassionate, I would encourage you bring that to God.

01:01:07.831 --> 01:01:13.980
As you're opening this book, pray that prayer, say Father in Heaven, show me your compassion in this book.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:23.794
You know what, if you are praying to see God as gracious and as loving, this is really good.

01:01:23.938 --> 01:01:27.462
place to go because he's going to teach it over and over.

01:01:27.702 --> 01:01:30.125
And the reason he teaches it over and over is because we need to know that.

01:01:30.525 --> 01:01:31.706
That's a good question to have.

01:01:31.746 --> 01:01:34.029
That's a very typical question.

01:01:34.750 --> 01:01:43.779
And that's one of the reasons he gave us the Scriptures to show us again and again his steadfast love and faithfulness, his compassion, his love.

01:01:43.800 --> 01:01:45.441
So have a question like that.

01:01:45.581 --> 01:01:48.745
Bring it to God's Word as you read.

01:01:49.245 --> 01:01:51.047
And just feel free.

01:01:51.468 --> 01:01:53.490
If you come across a verse about love,

01:01:54.082 --> 01:01:59.009
about compassion, about his grace, make that your verse for meditation.

01:02:00.031 --> 01:02:06.560
Just, I mean, modern people, you can feel like this sense of, oh, I need to spend equal amount of time on all the Bible.

01:02:06.580 --> 01:02:07.482
No, you don't.

01:02:08.583 --> 01:02:23.986
If that's your question, come across a love passage, linger there, and pray that you would experience that God means for us to experience his love, his compassion, not just read about it, that we would,

01:02:24.546 --> 01:02:32.760
come into communion with God himself in the realities he talks about in the book, not just the words of the book, the words are meant to get us to realities.

01:02:33.521 --> 01:02:37.768
Pray that way, seek it, and see how he shows up and answers.

01:02:38.529 --> 01:02:39.491
Great, awesome.

